1. Markets suffered through another day of losses, prompting Christine Lagarde, the head of the International Monetary Fund, to offer a cautious assessment of the world’s economy. “Asia as a region is still expected to lead global growth,” she said on a visit to Indonesia. “But even here, the pace is turning out slower than expected.”

The Dow, the S.&P. 500 and the Nasdaq all closed down nearly 3 percent.